  "local_port": 40998,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are movies that everyone should see?",
  "response": "There are countless movies that have made significant impacts on cinema, culture, or storytelling. Here\u2019s a list of films across various genres and eras that many people consider must-sees:\n\n### Classic Films\n1. **Casablanca** (1942) - A poignant love story set against the backdrop of World War II.\n2. **Citizen Kane** (1941) - Often cited as one of the greatest films of all time, it explores the life of a media mogul.\n3. **Gone with the Wind** (1939) - An epic romance set during the American Civil War.\n\n### Drama\n4. **The Godfather** (1972) - A powerful portrayal of a mafia family and the complexities of love and loyalty.\n5. **Schindler's List** (1993) - A harrowing tale of the Holocaust that highlights the power of one individual's choices.\n6. **12 Angry Men** (1957) - A gripping courtroom drama that explores themes of justice and moral responsibility.\n\n### Science Fiction\n7. **2001: A Space Odyssey** (1968) - A groundbreaking film that explores evolution, artificial intelligence, and the nature of existence.\n8. **Blade Runner** (1982) - A visually stunning film that questions what it means to be human in a dystopian future.\n\n### Animation\n9. **Spirited Away** (2001) - A beautifully crafted Japanese animated film that captivates audiences with its imaginative storytelling.\n10. **Toy Story** (1995) - The first fully computer-animated feature that changed the animation landscape forever.\n\n### Thriller/Suspense\n11. **Psycho** (1960) - Alfred Hitchcock's classic horror-thriller that redefined the genre.\n12. **Seven** (1995) - A dark and gripping exploration of morality in a serial-killer narrative.\n\n### Comedy\n13. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) - A classic screwball comedy featuring cross-dressing and hijinks.\n14. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail** (1975) - A cult classic that parodies the Arthurian legend with absurd humor.\n\n### Adventure/Fantasy\n15. **The Wizard of Oz** (1939) - A timeless adventure filled with memorable characters and musical numbers.\n16. **The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring** (2001) - A sweeping epic that brings J.R.R. Tolkien\u2019s world to life.\n\n### Contemporary Films\n17. **Parasite** (2019) - A genre-bending film that critiques class disparity in South Korea.\n18. **Moonlight** (2016) - A beautifully told coming-of-age story that explores identity and connection.\n\n### Documentaries\n19. **13th** (2016) - A powerful exploration of race, justice, and mass incarceration in the United States.\n20. **Won't You Be My Neighbor?** (2018) - A heartwarming look at the life and legacy of Fred Rogers.\n\n### International Films\n21. **Seven Samurai** (1954) - A cornerstone of world cinema, this Akira Kurosawa film has influenced countless filmmakers.\n22. **Am\u00e9lie** (2001) - A whimsical look at life in Paris, filled with charm and visual delight.\n\nThis list offers a diverse array of films, showcasing different genres, themes, and styles that have resonated with audiences over the years.",
